quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  51,24,Has there come to you the story of Abraham’s honored guests
  51,25,"When they came to him and said, “Peace.” He said, “Upon you be peace.” [saying to himself] “Unknown people!”"
  51,26,"Then he went quickly to his household, and came with a fat [roasted] calf"
  51,27,"and placed it before them and said, “Will you not eat?”"
  51,28,"He perceived a fear of them. They said, “Do not be afraid,” and gave him glad tidings of a knowledgeable son"
  51,29,"His wife cried out loud, and struck her face [in astonishment] and said, “[I am] a barren old woman!”"
  51,30,"They said, “This is what your Lord said. Indeed, He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing.”"
  51,31,"Abraham said, “Then what is your mission, O messengers?”"
  51,32,"They said, “We have been sent to a wicked people"
  51,33,to send down upon them stones of clay
  51,34,marked by your Lord for the transgressors.”
  51,35,We brought out those believers who were there
  51,36,"but We only found in it one Muslim household [Lot's family]"
  51,37,"And We left there a sign [as a lesson] for those who fear the painful punishment"
  51,38,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Moses when We sent him to Pharaoh with compelling proofs"
  51,39,"But he and his supporters turned away, and he said about [Moses], “A magician or a madman!”"
  51,40,"So We seized him and his soldiers, and cast them into the sea while he was blameworthy"
  51,41,"And [there is a sign in the story of] ‘Ād, when We sent against them the devastating barren wind"
  51,42,It spared nothing it came upon except that it reduced it to ruin and decay
  51,43,"And [there is a sign in the story of] Thamūd, when they were told, “Enjoy yourselves for a while.”"
  51,44,"But they rebelled against the command of their Lord, so the thunderbolt seized them, while they were looking on"
  51,45,"They could not withstand it, nor could they ward it off"
  51,46,"And the people of Noah [were also destroyed] before them. They were indeed a rebellious people"